Author:
Vol / Page:  2
Edition:
Quote:  At the conclusion of the lecture, Mr. Lyon put us in possession of a curious fact connected with the development of the mineral wealth of the southern island, namely that the greenstone, or <i>poonamor</i>, of the natives, a species of talc slate, is in such demand in the Chinese market for the manufacture of their idols, ornaments, &c., that as much as GBP1500 per ton can be had for it.
